        content: "type: search_result\ntitle: Best cafés for working in Berlin — Handpicked Berlin\nurl: \"https://handpickedberlin.com/best-cafes-to-work-in-berlin/\"\ndescription: \"(multiple locations including Mitte, Kreuzberg, Tempelhof, and Schöneberg) Sankt Oberholz offers a variety of flexible workspace solutions in Berlin, including coworking spaces. Catering to freelancers and companies alike, the café emphasizes ...\"\npage_age: \"March 25, 2025\"\nprofile_name: Handpicked Berlin\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/lf75Tj1qN_mErLezUulk0OdhoCvSBmtSbz87RrTqt1g/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvYzQ2YWJjMGU4/NjBmYzU2ZjcwZjYy/YjkyNzA5YzQ3ZDEw/MjZjYmE0Y2NlZmZm/Y2FlODFiYzYyNTYz/MzAyY2EzZC9oYW5k/cGlja2VkYmVybGlu/LmNvbS8\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/2_QcgcPVjMnmDzj-t8scCEUJCkrPkxM_7A8i6qOXmcI/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9oYW5k/cGlja2VkYmVybGlu/LmNvbS9fYXN0cm8v/YmVybGluLWNhZmVz/LkRJMGMzMTVGLmpw/Zw\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://handpickedberlin.com/_astro/berlin-cafes.DI0c315F.jpg\"\nextra_snippets: \"Though some cafés, which are usually categorized as coworking space, designate quiet zones in order to work without distractions. The atmosphere is a bit more elusive and is dependent on specific interests, whether trendy, minimalist, traditional, or whimsical. ... An understanding of laptop use, longer stays, and a relaxed approach to table turnover is key. Staff friendliness might be an important factor, as there usually isn’t a standard guideline for how long a patron can use a table.|If you need a quiet space to work, early weekend mornings may give you the most peaceful experience. The average cup of coffee will usually cost between €3.00 and €6.00, depending on the type of coffee and any add-ons, such as milk. Espresso will cost less. Though many cafés in Berlin are laptop-friendly, some might impose time limits, especially during peak hours.|While many cafés in Berlin are laptop-friendly, some might impose time limits during peak hours. It’s good practice to purchase items regularly if you’re planning an extended stay. Public libraries offer free entry, quiet environments, free Wi-Fi, and numerous power outlets with no time limits.|(multiple locations including Mitte, Kreuzberg, Tempelhof, and Schöneberg) Sankt Oberholz offers a variety of flexible workspace solutions in Berlin, including coworking spaces. Catering to freelancers and companies alike, the café emphasizes a collaborative atmosphere that enhances productivity and community engagement. Sankt Oberholz is known for its friendly service and a vibrant atmosphere that caters to both work and leisure.\"\nhash: 28262116e8123b3e\nembed_ref: handpickedberlin.com-tLD\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
