        embed_id: "44932a01-06a3-406a-8695-1f74b24b5986",
        type: "website",
        content: "type: search_result\ntitle: \"BERLIN: 50+ Laptop & Work-Friendly Cafés in Berlin — Natalie Etc\"\nurl: \"https://www.natalieetc.com/home/9-laptop-work-friendly-cafes-in-berlin\"\ndescription: \"They are conveniently work-friendly all the time except for Sunday brunch, however in the afternoon (15:00 to 18:00) on Sundays you’re welcome to work on your laptop. If the front room is full or you’re looking for a quieter atmosphere you can head on to their second or third room which are also laptop-friendly.\"\npage_age: \"April 16, 2025\"\nprofile_name: Natalie Etc\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/3JZS1VO6n7BtAV9NWMjCay-JBJCv8ltUAkbNV8UcYxU/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvYWFmZjAyZTgw/MDk2MzVmZTQ4ZWJh/OWYxNjVlNDE5ZDMy/NTBmZTRhOGRlY2Rj/ZDYwMWU2MjNiMThk/ODBmZTkxOC93d3cu/bmF0YWxpZWV0Yy5j/b20v\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/gmgWVAutqv4Jvnnc2Z3ervsO2RJlbYRn3v9ibv2RFls/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL3N0YXRp/YzEuc3F1YXJlc3Bh/Y2UuY29tL3N0YXRp/Yy81ZDQ0Y2E2ZTI4/ZjA4ODAwMDFiN2E2/YTIvNWQ0NGNjMDlj/NTFkOTMwMDAxMTNi/MjhjLzVmOWMzZDU1/YzIxZmU3NGYwZmJk/NDM4NC8xNzQ0ODA1/OTIxMzc3L3VubmFt/ZWQlMkIlMjUyODIy/JTI1MjkuanBnP2Zv/cm1hdD0xNTAwdw\"\nthumbnail_original: \"http://static1.squarespace.com/static/5d44ca6e28f0880001b7a6a2/5d44cc09c51d93000113b28c/5f9c3d55c21fe74f0fbd4384/1744805921377/unnamed%2B%252822%2529.jpg?format=1500w\"\nextra_snippets: \"If you’re interested in a coworking pass for the day, it’s honestly a great deal considering the WiFi is even faster (plus secured), it’s quieter, and you get access to a number of amenities like printing and filtered water. The four-hour pass is €7, while the full-day pass is €15 and includes a café drink.|Codos Coffee is a sweet spot around Rosenthaler Platz, with all the makings of a great laptop-friendly café. It tends to stay quieter, there are outlets, there’s a decent amount of seating, and they have stamp cards. However, the WiFi is just okay. It worked very well for me for about 1.5 hours before starting to give me trouble.|There are four work-friendly areas: the entry room (which consists of mostly armchairs with coffee tables), the central courtyard, the main work room (which is a quiet zone), and the basement work room (which is a collaborative and talk-friendly space, popular for group projects).|They are conveniently work-friendly all the time except for Sunday brunch, however in the afternoon (15:00 to 18:00) on Sundays you’re welcome to work on your laptop. If the front room is full or you’re looking for a quieter atmosphere you can head on to their second or third room which are also laptop-friendly.\"\nhash: ef2d26d9b8e45134\nembed_ref: natalieetc.com-Kwz\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
